Sentencas: Cobalt-free small La3+-doped BaFeO3-delta is synthesized and systematically characterized towards application as an oxygen reduction electrode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) with oxygen-ion conducting electrolyte.
Titulo: La-doped BaFeO3-δ perovskite as a cobalt-free oxygen reduction electrode for solid oxide fuel cells with oxygen-ion conducting electrolyte

Sentencas: The formation of an oxygen vacancy-disordered perovskite oxide with cubic lattice symmetry is demonstrated by XRD, after the doping of only 5 mol% La3+ into BaFeO3-delta parent oxide with the formation of Ba0.95La0.05FeO3-delta (BLF).
Titulo: La-doped BaFeO3-δ perovskite as a cobalt-free oxygen reduction electrode for solid oxide fuel cells with oxygen-ion conducting electrolyte

Sentencas: The structural, thermal, electrical and electrochemical properties of BLF have been evaluated.
Titulo: La-doped BaFeO3-δ perovskite as a cobalt-free oxygen reduction electrode for solid oxide fuel cells with oxygen-ion conducting electrolyte

Sentencas: High structural stability, high thermal expansion coefficient, high oxygen vacancy concentration, and relatively low electrical conductivity, are demonstrated.
Titulo: La-doped BaFeO3-δ perovskite as a cobalt-free oxygen reduction electrode for solid oxide fuel cells with oxygen-ion conducting electrolyte

Sentencas: BLF shows a superior electrocatalytic activity, which is comparable to those state-of-the-art cobalt-based mixed conducting cathodes, in addition, it demonstrates a favorable long-term operational stability.
Titulo: La-doped BaFeO3-δ perovskite as a cobalt-free oxygen reduction electrode for solid oxide fuel cells with oxygen-ion conducting electrolyte

Sentencas: It thus promises as a new cathode candidate for IT-SOFCs with oxygen-ion conducting electrolyte.
Titulo: La-doped BaFeO3-δ perovskite as a cobalt-free oxygen reduction electrode for solid oxide fuel cells with oxygen-ion conducting electrolyte
